    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of tax used in Spanish colonial times. Each land owner or tenant had to pay an alcabala tax to the State to be able to carry out activities of buying and selling products in their respective establishments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
